'''Recycling antimatter''' pertains to recycling [[antiprotons]] and [[antihydrogen|antihydrogen atoms]].<ref name=Fermi> {{cite web | last =Riesselmann | first =Kurt | title =Recycling Antimatter Becomes Reality | website = | publisher =Fermi News. [[Fermilab]] | date =February 1, 2002 | url =http://www.fnal.gov/pub/ferminews/ferminews02-02-01/p1.html | doi = | accessdate =4 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=Kurt> {{cite web | last =Riesselmann | first =Kurt | title =Keeping Antiprotons Cool | website = | publisher =Fermi News. [[Fermilab]] | date =February 1, 2002 | url =http://www.fnal.gov/pub/ferminews/ferminews02-02-01/p1b.html | doi = | accessdate =4 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=nobel> {{cite web | first = Simon | last = van der Meer | authorlink = Simon van der Meer | title =Nobel Lecture: Stochastic Cooling and the Accumulation of Antiprotons | website = | publisher =Nobel Lectures, Physics 1981-1990 | date =8 December 1984 | url =https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1984/meer-lecture.html | doi = | accessdate =4 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=pham> {{cite journal | title =Antimatter Interferometry for Gravity Measurements | journal =[[Physical Review Letters]] | volume =112 | issue =12 | arxiv = 1308.1079 | doi = 10.1103/PhysRevLett.112.121102 | date =2014 | last1 =Hamilton | first1 =Paul | last2 =Zhmoginov | first2 =Andrey | last3 =Robicheaux | first3 =Francis | last4 =Fajans | first4 =Joel | last5 =Wurtele | first5 =Jonathan S. | last6 =Müller | first6 =Holger |bibcode = 2014PhRvL.112l1102H | pmid=24724644 | page=121102| url =http://www.escholarship.org/uc/item/5nz5q0qh }}</ref><ref name=regenfus> {{cite conference | last =Regenfus | first =Christian | title =Measurement of antimatter gravity with an (anti) matter wave interferometer | date = 26 September 2004 | url =http://indico.cern.ch/event/a043551/session/12/contribution/s18t16/material/0/0.pdf | accessdate = }} Anti-protons - Session 2. Villars meeting 22–28 September 2004.CERN.</ref><ref